From: NextOS Elite <noreply@nextos.local>
Subject: [PATCH] include/stdlib.h: delegate to system when HOSTCC

u-boot/include/stdlib.h é um shim que só inclui <malloc.h>. Mas como
ele é achado ANTES do system stdlib.h (via -I$(srctree)/include), as
host-tools que precisam de EXIT_FAILURE/exit/free/etc pegam esse shim
em vez do system real — erros 'EXIT_FAILURE undeclared'.

Fix: quando USE_HOSTCC, usa #include_next pra delegar pro próximo
<stdlib.h> no path (o system). Mantém comportamento original pro
target (cross-compile) — só malloc.h.

---
 include/stdlib.h | 8 +++++++-
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/include/stdlib.h b/include/stdlib.h
--- a/include/stdlib.h
+++ b/include/stdlib.h
@@ -7,6 +7,12 @@
 #ifndef __STDLIB_H_
 #define __STDLIB_H_
 
-#include <malloc.h>
+#ifdef USE_HOSTCC
+/* Build das tools: usa stdlib.h do sistema (EXIT_FAILURE, exit, etc). */
+#include_next <stdlib.h>
+#else
+/* Build target: só precisa do malloc shim. */
+#include <malloc.h>
+#endif
 
 #endif /* __STDLIB_H_ */
